      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Revkin, Andrew C</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Swiss Academy of Natural Sciences reports record melting of Swiss glaciers due to extended recent warming of climate; holds that some areas of ice retreated nearly 500 feet (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Swiss glaciers retreated last year at a pace not seen since systematic record keeping began in 1880, and the melting was a result of prolonged recent climate warming, not Europe's scorching summer heat wave, the Swiss Academy of Natural Sciences said. Some glaciers retreated nearly 500 feet, the academy said.</p>
        <p>Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
